
(1) Functional tests:

* How to install:

On Mac, using homebrew:

$ brew install phantomjs
$ brew install casperjs


(Alternatively, both can be installed with npm)

* To run all the tests:

$ casperjs test tests/*.js


(2) Acceptance tests:

First run a full browser emulator:

$ java -jar -Dwebdriver.chrome.driver=chromedriver selenium-server-standalone-3.8.1.jar

or 

$  phantomjs --webdriver=8643


you can choose one of the commands below:

$ Behat/bin/behat --tags @ok,@wip -v --stop-on-failure -c Behat/behat.yml # will run the scenarios tagged with @ok or @wip
$ Behat/bin/behat --tags ~@wip -v --stop-on-failure -c Behat/behat.yml # will run all the scenarios except those tagged with @wip
$ Behat/bin/behat  -v --stop-on-failure -c Behat/behat.yml # will run all the scenarios


Also make sure before running the suite the facebook test user has the gigadb app deauthorised by login as her and deauthorising the app in the Settings>Apps section. 